<div class="row-fluid border-bottom">
  <h3 class="intro">If you’ve ever dreamed of helping remote communities get equal access to water, feel compelled to stand up for animal rights, or inspired to share your passion for a sustainable food system with the next generation, the Faculty of Land and Food Systems (LFS) may be the right Faculty for you.
<br>
<br>To learn more about LFS and to see if it's the right fit for you, we invite you to visit beautiful Vancouver and <a href="https://www.landfood.ubc.ca/prospective/lfs-events/#campus">check out an on campus event</a> for prospective students. Our Academic Advisors also visit cities to talk about LFS; see if they're coming <a href="https://www.landfood.ubc.ca/prospective/lfs-events/#community">to your community</a>.</h3>
</div>
<div class="row-fluid border-bottom" id="campus">
  <h1>On Campus</h1>
<h3>UBC Welcomes You</h3>
<p>Excited to accept your offer to LFS?  Don't miss out on <b>UBC Welcomes You</b> this spring!  More details of the day will follow soon, but mark your calendar to join us at UBC's Vancouver campus on <b>Saturday, April 27</b> from <b>9:30am to 12:30pm</b> for a half-day full of activities, information and opportunities to meet and learn from LFS students, staff and faculty.  Joining us on this day will ensure you're best prepared for your year ahead.  Keep your eyes on your email inbox for an invite, and check <a href="https://you.ubc.ca/tours-info-sessions/campus-tours-events/on-campus-events/">here</a> for updates.  (More details will also be posted here closer to the date!)</div>
<div class="row-fluid border-bottom" id="community">
  <h1>In Your Community</h1>
<p><h3>Seattle, Washington, USA</h3>
<p>Sarah, our Academic Advisor for international students, will be joining the UBC International Student Recruitment team in Seattle for the <b>UBC Applicant Information Event</b>.
<p><ul>
<li><b>When:</b> Saturday, March 23, 2019</li>
<li><b>Details:</b> Students will be invited directly, so register via the email you receive, and look out for the LFS table to connect with Sarah at the event!</li></ul
<p><h3>San Francisco (San Mateo), California, USA</h3>
<p> Sarah, our Academic Advisor for international students, will be joining the UBC International Student Recruitment team in San Francisco for the <b>UBC Applicant Information Event</b>.  You’ll also get the opportunity to meet LFS faculty member, <a href="https://www.landfood.ubc.ca/marina-von-keyserlingk/">Nina Von Keyserlingk</a>, NSERC Industrial Research Chair and Professor in our Animal Welfare program.  Nina will be the faculty keynote at this event!
<p><ul>
<li><b>When:</b> Saturday, March 30, 2019</li>
<li><b>Details:</b> Students will be invited directly, so register via the email you receive, and look out for the LFS table to connect with Sarah and Nina at the event!</li></ul
