<p>We look forward to meeting newly-admitted students when we join our colleagues from the UBC recruitment teams at <b>UBC Welcomes You</b> and <b>UBC Applicant Information Events</b> in communities across Canada, the US and around the world this spring to welcome all newly-admitted students to LFS and UBC.  Check <a href="https://you.ubc.ca/tours-info-sessions/ubc-visits/">here</a> for updates, and watch your email inbox for invites to these events. Whether we’re coming to your hometown or not, you are always welcome to <a href="https://www.landfood.ubc.ca/student-services/#connect">contact LFS Student Services</a> with your questions at any time - we're always happy to help!</p></ul>
<p>Ready to jump in?  See your <a href="https://www.landfood.ubc.ca/prospective/#degree">‘Degree at a Glance,’</a> or learn about what it’s like to be a student in LFS by reading the <a href="https://www.landfood.ubc.ca/featured-profiles/">featured profiles</a> of Food, Nutrition and Health students, Aki and Jeff, Applied Biology student, Courtney and Global Resource Systems student, Ainsley.  New student profiles are being updated every month, so be sure to check back often for more insight to the LFS student experience. 
